body_html:
Op type not registered 'Identity' in binary running on localhost. Make sure the Op and Kernel are registered in the binary running in this process.

These error messages appear to be showing that the ops you need (Sin, Identity etc) are not being included in your optimized libtensorflow_inference.so. I'm not sure why this would happen for your "Attempt 3" if it really is using the full TensorFlow library, but it certainly explains the failures for "Attempt 1" and "Attempt 2".

In my blog post, see the Checking the list of operations in ops_to_register.h section. You will need to add the missing ops to the ops_to_register.h file, and rebuild libtensorflow_inference.so. This reduced list of ops is the reason that we're able to create smaller versions of the TensorFlow library (i.e. we're trying to discard all the unneeded ops).

You might find Pete Warden's free eBook Building Mobile Applications with TensorFlow useful on this topic. Good luck!

body:
> Op type not registered 'Identity' in binary running on localhost. Make sure the Op and Kernel are registered in the binary running in this process.

These error messages appear to be showing that the ops you need (`Sin`, `Identity` etc) are not being included in your optimized libtensorflow_inference.so.  I'm not sure why this would happen for your "Attempt 3" if it really is using the full TensorFlow library, but it certainly explains the failures for "Attempt 1" and "Attempt 2".

In [my blog post](https://medium.com/@daj/how-to-shrink-the-tensorflow-android-inference-library-cb698facf758), see the `Checking the list of operations in ops_to_register.h` section.  You will need to add the missing ops to the `ops_to_register.h` file, and rebuild libtensorflow_inference.so.  This reduced list of ops is the reason that we're able to create smaller versions of the TensorFlow library (i.e. we're trying to discard all the unneeded ops).

You might find Pete Warden's free eBook [Building Mobile Applications with TensorFlow](http://www.oreilly.com/data/free/building-mobile-applications-with-tensorflow.csp) useful on this topic.  Good luck!
